The vision itself, has little, if any, bearing upon the general history of the reign, and it is just such an incident as we might be inclined to neglect or expunge as an idle tale. But the legend affords 3 curious proof how useful the slightest notices relating to individuals may be, in completing the chain of historical evidence 3 and that matters, appearing at first sight without any specific application to au thentic history, may nevertheless confirm the tes- timony afforded by the more trust-worthy portions of the chronicler. By this tran- sient glimpse of Fitz Osbert in the cha- racter of 3 Crusader, we can trace the source of that intimacy with King Richard, which afterwards enabled him to take a most influential station in the civic community.
